===Adjective===<!-- or perhaps a quantifier, or both -->
Sometimes called a [[determiner]]<br>
'''neither'''

# not [[one]] of two; not [[either]]
#* '''neither''' definition seems correct

====Translations====
{{Translations requested}}
* {{fr}}: [[ni]]

===Pronoun===
'''neither'''

# not either one
#* because '''neither''' is correct

===Translations===
*{{fr}}:  neither X nor Y: ''ni'' X ''ni'' Y.
*German: [[keine]]
*Hindi: [[भी नहीं]]

===Conjunction===
'''neither'''

# not either (used with [[nor]])
#* '''neither''' I nor you like it
# also not
#* if you won’t correct it, '''neither''' will I

===Adverb===
'''neither'''

# similarly not
#* just as you would not correct it, neither would I

===Usage notes===
*'''Neither''' is used to mean none of two.  Use [[none]] with more than two things.
*There is considerable variation in regards to the number of the verb employed with this construction.

